Simple Python Calculator
This is a beginner-friendly Python program that acts as a simple calculator, allowing users to perform basic arithmetic operations. It demonstrates the use of Python functions and interactive input handling.

Features
The calculator supports the following operations:

Addition (+)
Subtraction (-)
Multiplication (*)
Division (/)
Exponentiation (**)
Modulus (remainder, %)
Floor Division (quotient, //)
How to Use:
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Simple-Python-Calculator.git  
Run the program:
python calculator.py  
Select an operation by entering the corresponding number (1â€“7).
Input two numbers when prompted.
View the result of the selected operation.
Example:

Select option:  
1. Add  
2. Subtract  
3. Multiplication  
4. Divide  
5. Power  
6. Modulus  
7. Floor Divide  

Enter choice (1/2/3/4/5/6/7): 1  
Enter first number: 10  
Enter second number: 5  
10 + 5 = 15 

Key Learning Points:

Function implementation for modularity
Handling user input and validating choices
Performing various arithmetic operations


